This paper presents a model for joint aspect identification and sentiment analysis in product reviews, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques for model inference, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper's focus on discovering highly-rated or inconsistent aspects of a product aligns with the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
